)\n* {{Citation |last=Keeling |first=Drew |date=27 May 2015 |url=http://whartonmagazine.com/blogs/business-history-dividends-of-waterloo/ |title=The Dividends of Waterloo|accessdate=3 June 2015}}\n* {{Citation |last=Kennedy |first=Paul |year=1987 |title=The Rise and Fall of Great Powers |publisher= New York: Random House}}\n* {{Citation |last=Kincaid |first=Captain J. |year=2006 |chapter=The Final Attack The Rifle Brigade Advance 7 pm 18 June 1815 |editor-last=Lewis-Stemple |editor-first=John |title=England: The Autobiography: 2,000 Years of English History by Those Who Saw it Happen |edition=reprint |location=UK |publisher=Penguin |isbn=978-0-14-192869-2 |pages=[https://books.google.com/books?id=kRArkAr-yxoC&pg=PT434 434]\u2013436}}\n* {{citation |last=Kottasova |first=Ivana |date=10 June 2015 |url=http://money.cnn.com/2015/06/10/news/waterloo-coin-belgium-france/index.html|title=France's new Waterloo? Euro coin marks Napoleon's defeat|work=CNNMoney}}\n* {{citation |last=Lamar |first=Glenn J. |year=2000 |title=J\u00e9r\u00f4me Bonaparte: The War Years, 1800\u20131815|publisher=Greenwood Press|isbn=978-0-313-30997-7 |page=119 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=0NBnAAAAMAAJ}}\n* {{Citation |last=Longford |first=Elizabeth |authorlink=Elizabeth Longford |year=1971 |title=Wellington the Years of the Sword |publisher=London: Panther| isbn=978-0-586-03548-1}}\n* {{Citation |last=Low |first=E. Bruce |year=1911 |chapter=The Waterloo Papers |editor-last=MacBride |editor-first= M. |title=With Napoleon at Waterloo |location=London |chapter-url=https://archive.org/details/withnapoleonatwa00macbuoft}}\n* {{Citation |last=Lozier |first=J.F. |date=18 June 2010 |url=http://www.napoleon-series.org/faq/c_horses.html |title=What was the name of Napoleon's horse? |publisher= The Napoleon Series |accessdate=29 March 2009}}\n* {{Citation |last=Mantle |first=Robert |date=December 2000 |title=Prussian Reserve Infantry 1813\u20131815: Part II: Organisation |publisher=Napoleonic Associat