hive.org/details/waterloocampaign0000nofi }}\n* {{citation |last1=Oman |first1=Charles |last2=Hall |first2=John A. |year=1902 |title=A History of the Peninsular War |publisher=Clarendon Press |page=[https://books.google.com/books?id=q6pBAQAAMAAJ 119]}}\n* {{Citation |last=Palmer |first=R.R. |year=1956 |title=A History of the Modern World |publisher= New York: Knopf}}\n* {{citation |last=Parkinson |first=Roger |year=2000 |title=Hussar General: The Life of Bl\u00fccher, Man of Waterloo |publisher=Wordsworth Military Library |isbn=978-1840222531 |pages=[https://books.google.com/books?id=x58TZVEU_Q4C&lpg=PP1&pg=PA240 240]\u2013241}}\n* {{Citation |last=Parry |first=D.H. |year=1900 |chapterurl=http://gaslight.mtroyal.ab.ca/waterloo.htm |chapter=Waterloo |title=Battle of the nineteenth century |volume=1 |publisher=London: Cassell and Company |accessdate=14 September 2007 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081216071449/http://gaslight.mtroyal.ab.ca/waterloo.htm |archivedate=16 December 2008 |df=dmy-all }}\n* {{citation |last=Paton |first=Callum |date=5 April 2015 |url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sciencetech/article-3026442/200-year-old-skeleton-hunchback-soldier-killed-battle-Waterloo-Belgian-car-park-believed-trained-Sussex.html |title=Skeleton of soldier killed at Waterloo discovered under a car park like Richard III |newspaper=Daily Mail Online}}\n* {{Citation |last=Pawly |first=Ronald |title=Wellington's Belgian Allies |series=Men at Arms nr 98. 1815 |publisher=Osprey |year=2001 |pages=37\u201343 |isbn=978-1-84176-158-9}}\n* {{Citation |last=Paxton |first=Robert O. |year=1985 |title=Europe in the 20th Century |publisher= Orlando: Harcourt Brace Jovanovich}}\n* {{Citation |last=Peel |first=Hugues Van |date=11 December 2012 |title=Le soldat retrouv\u00e9 sur le site de Waterloo serait Hanovrien |publisher=[[RTBF]] |url=http://www.rtbf.be/info/regions/detail_le-soldat-retrouve-sur-le-site-de-waterloo-etait-prussien?id=7890492 |language=French}}\n* {