um International Publishing Group |isbn=978-0-8264-2590-4 |page=[https://books.google.com/books?id=0AgapOzStrAC&pg=PA32 327]}}\n* {{Citation |last=Cotton |first=Edward |year=1849 |title=A voice from Waterloo. A history of the battle, on 18 June 1815.| publisher=London: B.L. Green}}\n* {{Citation |last=Creasy |first=Sir Edward |year=1877 |url=http://www.gutenberg.org/etext/4061 |title=The Fifteen Decisive Battles of the World: from Marathon to Waterloo |publisher=London: Richard Bentley & Son |isbn=978-0-306-80559-2}}\n* {{Citation |last=Davies |first=Huw |year=2012 |title=Wellington's Wars: The Making of a Military Genius |edition=illustrated |publisher=Yale University Press |isbn=978-0-300-16417-6 |page=[https://books.google.com/books?id=_sCxNtg1H8IC&pg=PA244 244]}}\n* {{Citation |last=Eenens |first=A.M |authorlink=Alexis-Michel Eenens |year=1879 |title=\"Dissertation sur la participation des troupes des Pays-Bas a la campagne de 1815 en Belgique\", in: Societ\u00e9 royale des beaux arts et de lit\u00e9rature de Gand, Messager des Sciences Historiques |publisher=Vanderhaegen |location=Gand}}\n* {{Citation| last= Comte d'Erlon| first= Jean-Baptiste Drouet| authorlink= Jean-Baptiste Drouet, Comte d'Erlon| year= 1815| title= Drouet's account of Waterloo to the French Parliament| url= http://www.napoleonbonaparte.nl/newspaper/dedham/drouet.html| publisher= Napoleon Bonaparte Internet Guide| accessdate= 14 September 2007| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20071008105416/http://www.napoleonbonaparte.nl/newspaper/dedham/drouet.html| archivedate= 8 October 2007| url-status= dead}}\n* {{Citation |last=Esposito |first=Vincent Joseph| last2=Elting| first2=John |year=1999 |title=A Military History and Atlas of the Napoleonic Wars| publisher=Greenhill|isbn=978-1-85367-346-7}}\n* {{Citation |last=Field |first=Andrew W. |year=2013 |title= Waterloo The French Perspective |location=Great Britain |publisher=Pen & Sword Books |isbn=978-1-78159-043-0}}\n* {{Citation| last=Fitchett |first=W.H. |year=2006 |origyear=1897 |title=Deeds that Won the Empire. Historic Battle Scenes |url=http://www.gutenberg.org/etext/19255 |location=London |publisher=John Murray |chapter-url=http://www.gutenberg.org/files/19255/19255-h/19255-h.htm#chap1900 |chapter=Chapter: King-making Waterloo}} ([[Project Gutenberg]])\n* {{Citation |last=Fletcher |first=Ian |year=1994 |title=Wellington's Foot Guards |volume=52 of Elite Series |edition=illustrated |publisher=Osprey Publishing|isbn=978-1-85532-392-6}}\n* {{Citation |last=Fletcher |first=Ian |year=1999 |title=Galloping at Everything: The British Cavalry in the Peninsula and at Waterloo 1808\u201315|publisher=Spellmount|place= Staplehurst|isbn=978-1-86227-016-9}}\n* {{Citation |last=Fletcher |first=Ian |year=2001 |title=A Desperate Business: Wellington, The British Army and the Waterloo Campaign'', Spellmount|place=Staplehurst, Kent}}\n* {{Citation |last=Frye |first=W.E. |year=2004 |origyear=1908 |url=http://www.gutenberg.org/ebooks/10939 |title=After Waterloo: Reminiscences of European Travel 1815\u20131819| publisher=[[Project Gutenberg]]| accessdate=29 April 2015}}\n* {{Citation| last=Glover |first=G. |year=2004 |title= Letters from the Battle of Waterloo: the unpublished correspondence by Anglo-allied officers from the Siborne papers |location=London |publisher=Greenhill |isbn=978-1-85367-597-3}}\n* {{Citation |last=Glover |first=Gareth |title=From Corunna to Waterloo: the Letters and Journals of Two Napoleonic Hussars, 1801\u20131816 |location=London |publisher=Greenhill Books |year=2007}}\n* {{Citation|first1=Gareth|last1=Glover|title=Waterloo: Myth and Reality|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=GfpsBQAAQBAJ|year=2014|publisher=Pen and Sword|isbn=978-1-78159-356-1}}\n* {{Citation |last=Grant |first=Charles |year=1972 |title=Royal Scots Greys (Men-at-Arms)|publisher=Osprey |isbn=978-0-85045-059-0}}\n* {{Citation |last=Gronow |first=R.H. |authorlink=Rees Howell Gronow |year=1862 |url=http://www.gutenberg.org/